HEADWORD: Toilinette
<hw>Toi`li*nette"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>toilinet</ets>. See <er>Toil</er> a net.]</ety> <def>A cloth, the
weft of which is of woolen yarn, and the warp of cotton and silk, --
used for waistcoats.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toilless</ent>⟦br⟧
